(firstQuint)Effect of Statins on IgG, IgA and IgM Level in Chronic Hemodialysis Patients.

 This study is a randomized controlled trial of statins effect on serum IgG, IgA and IgM level on chronic hemodialysis patients in Bandarabbas.

 The study is carried out in Hormozgan, Iran.

 Seventy four patient were randomized either to receive atorvastatin in addition of usual treatment or not.

 The primary outcomes were serum IgG,IgA and IgM level.

 The secondary outcome was drug side effects.

